bug.short_desc: wireshark-cli %post scriptlet fails with: line 2: /usr/bin/udevadm: No such file or directory

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1148477 root.log
Description of problem:
Basically this:
DEBUG util.py:417: /var/tmp/rpm-tmp.547b9v: line 2: /usr/bin/udevadm: No such file or directory DEBUG util.py:417: warning: %post(wireshark-cli-2.0.2-1.fc25.x86_64) scriptlet failed, exit status 127
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
wireshark-cli-2.0.2-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible:
At least once. It happened in Koji here: https://kojipkgs.fedoraproject.org//work/tasks/3646/13713646/root.log
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 25 development cycle. Changing version to '25'.
